gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: QUADRANGLES_24K_USGS_IN is a polygon shapefile defining the boundaries of the USGS 7.5-minute (1:24,000-scale) quadrangles which cover the state of Indiana. Dates of publication and photorevision of paper quadrangle maps published by the U.S. Geological Survey are also provided.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This data set will help identify a quadrangle when trying to locate the most recent version of a paper quadrangle. It will also help determine if the most recent version of a digital copy has been obtained.

gmd:credit.gco:CharacterString: Indiana Statewide GIS database was produced under an Indiana Department of Transportation contract. Data is from the USGS published by Geocommunity. Acknowledgment of U.S. Geological Survey would be appreciated in products derived from these data.

gmd:supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString: Boundaries were created by the USGS, published by Geocommunity <http://www.gisdatadepot.com>, and processed by Bernardin, Lochmueller and Associates. Dates of publication and photorevision of paper quadrangle maps published by the U.S. Geological Survey were compiled by Karen Like, Indiana Geological Survey.

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Complete to the state of Indiana

All dates were collected from the paper United States Geological Survey 7.5-minute quadrangles available in Publication Sales at the Indiana Geological Survey. A list of the version dates was printed from the United States Geological Survey web site for a cross-check to make sure all current versions were available. If the dates did not match the digital raster graphics (DRGs) were checked and the United States Geological Survey was called to verify dates. The dates were then checked for typographical errors from notes to final copy by two Indiana Geological Survey employees. The original quadrangle names that accompanied the line work were checked and corrected to match the actual paper quadrangle names.
No tests have been performed, but use with USGS DRGs and aerial photographs have shown accurate placement.
Vertical accuracy was not a factor in the digital production of the data set.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: USGS digital 24K Quadrangle boundaries were obtained and published for download by geocommunity.
The source file "QUAD24" downloaded from the website and converted to a shapefile in UTM Zone 16, NAD83.

The converted file "QUADRANGLES_24K_USGS_IN" contains the fields 'Area' and 'Perimeter'. These fields were re-calculated using the ESRI syntax: Shape.returnarea and Shape.returnlength to reflect the changes in these fields when the shapefile was converted to UTM Zone 16 NAD83.

This metadata file was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit, v. 2.6.1) and MP (Metadata Parser, v. 2.7.1) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (United States Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected, except that no values were assigned to "Abscissa_Resolution" and "Ordinate_Resolution."

In ESRI ArView v. 3.2, a shapefile named "QUADINDEX_24K_USGS_IN" was joined to the shapefile named QUADRANGLES_24K_USGS_IN, using the field named "QUAD2" from QUADINDEX_24K_USGS_IN and the field named "NAME" from QUADRANGLES_24K_USGS_IN. The following fields were retained from QUADINDEX_24K_USGS_IN: "Map_date," "Phot_rev," "Phot_insp," and "Minor_rev." All other field derived from QUADINDEX_24K_USGS_IN were removed.
Georeferenced grid of USGS 7.5-minute quadrangle boundaries attributed with quad name and reference code.
